"params": [{"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "edge_match", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "", "xref": null, "params": [{"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "dict", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "all_solutions", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "return_integers", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "variant", "type": {"name": "VF3_VARIANTS_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "VF3_VARIANTS_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "num_threads", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["The core routine of the VF3Py library. It solves the subgraph isomorphism problem, i.e. finds ways to match nodes of `subgraph` with some/all nodes of `graph`. Only NetworkX graphs are accepted (either nx.Graph or nx.DiGraph). **NOTE**: It is not practical to call this function directly -- use one of the front-end functions instead: `are_isomorphic`, `get_exact_isomorphisms`, `get_automorphisms`, `has_subgraph`, `get_subgraph_isomorphisms`.\n\nArgs:\n\n: \\{SUBGRAPH}\n  \\{LARGE_GRAPH}\n  \\{NODE_MATCH}\n  \\{EDGE_MATCH}\n  \\{ALL_SOLUTIONS}\n  \\{RETURN_INTEGERS}\n  \\{VARIANT}\n  \\{NUM_THREADS}\n  \\{VERBOSE}\n\nReturns:\n\n: List\\[Dict\\]: List of subgraph->graph isomorphisms. Each isomorphism is represented by a dict that maps: 'subgraph' labels -> 'graph' labels.\n"]}, {"name": "vf3py._strict_isomorphisms", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "graphA", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "graphB", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vf3py._monomorphisms", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "graphA", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "graphB", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "vf3py.are_isomorphic", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "source_graph", "type": {"name": "GRAPH_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "GRAPH_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "target_graph", "type": {"name": "GRAPH_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "GRAPH_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "get_mapping", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}]}, "documentation": ["Check if two graphs are isomorphic. This includes checks for number of nodes - `are_isomorphic` always returns False if two graphs have different number of nodes, as opposed to graph-subgraph isomorphisms.\n\nArgs:\n\n: \\{FIRST_GRAPH}\n  \\{SECOND_GRAPH} Swap between source_graph \\<-> target_graph changes nothing.\n  \\{NODE_MATCH}\n  \\{EDGE_MATCH}\n  \\{VARIANT}\n  \\{NUM_THREADS}\n  \\{VERBOSE}\n\nReturns:\n\n: bool: True if graphs are isomorphic, False - otherwise.\n  Also, optionally returns Dict | None. The Dict represents the mapping 'target_graph' labels -> 'source_graph' labels. Returned only if get_mapping set to True.\n", "FRONT-END FUNCTIONS", "Exact matches"]}, {"name": "vf3py.get_exact_isomorphisms", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "source_graph", "type": {"name": "GRAPH_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "GRAPH_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "target_graph", "type": {"name": "GRAPH_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "GRAPH_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Get a list of all isomorphisms between two NetworkX graphs. This includes checks for number of nodes - `get_exact_isomorphisms` always returns `[]` if two graphs have different number of nodes, as opposed to graph-subgraph isomorphisms.\n\nArgs:\n\n: \\{FIRST_GRAPH}\n  \\{SECOND_GRAPH} Swap between source_graph \\<-> target_graph swaps keys with values in the resulting isomorphisms dicts.\n  \\{NODE_MATCH}\n  \\{EDGE_MATCH}\n  \\{RETURN_INTEGERS}\n  \\{VARIANT}\n  \\{NUM_THREADS}\n  \\{VERBOSE}\n\nReturns:\n\n: List\\[Dict\\]: List of source_graph\\<->target_graph isomorphisms. Each isomorphism is represented by a dict that maps: 'target_graph' labels -> 'source_graph' labels.\n"]}, {"name": "vf3py.get_automorphisms", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "graph", "type": {"name": "GRAPH_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "GRAPH_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Dict", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Dict", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Get isomorphic mappings of NetworkX graph onto itself (automorphism).\n\nArgs:\n    {ANY_GRAPH}\n    {NODE_MATCH}\n    {EDGE_MATCH}\n    {RETURN_INTEGERS}\n    {VARIANT}\n    {NUM_THREADS}\n    {VERBOSE}\n\nReturns:\n    List[Dict]: List of graph<->graph isomorphisms (represented as dicts)."]}, {"name": "vf3py.has_subgraph", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "subgraph", "type": {"name": "GRAPH_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "GRAPH_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "graph", "type": {"name": "GRAPH_TYPE", "xref": {"fqname": "GRAPH_TYPE", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "get_mapping", "type": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "Tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std